FYI: @smolnar82

As of [AMBARI-23354](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMBARI-23354), you will need to set `sso-configuration/ambari.sso.manage_services` to true to enable the feature. So the CLI shoudl ask the user if they want to allow Ambari to manage SSO configurations for installed services. If yes, then the user should be presented with the services to enabled this for. 

For example
```
AAAAB3NzaC1yc2EAAAADAQABAAABAQD....

Manage SSO for installed services [y/n] (n)? y
Use SSO for all services [y/n] (y)? n
Use SSO for Ambari [y/n] (y)? y
Use SSO for HDFS [y/n] (y)? y
Use SSO for YARN [y/n] (y)? y
...
Use SSO for ZOOKEEPER [y/n] (y)? n
Do you want to configure advanced properties [y/n] (n) ?
```
```
AAAAB3NzaC1yc2EAAAADAQABAAABAQD....

Manage SSO for installed services [y/n] (n)? n
Do you want to configure advanced properties [y/n] (n) ?
```
